David Duffield

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

For the sports commentator, see David Duffield (sports commentator).


David Duffield



David Duffield (2005)



Born
1941 (age 75–76)


Nationality
American


Alma mater
Cornell University


Occupation
Chairman of Workday, Inc.


Net worth
US$4.4 billion (June 2016)[1]


David Duffield (born 1941) is an American businessman in the software industry. He is the co-founder and former chairman of PeopleSoft, the co-founder and co-CEO at Workday, Inc., and has been on the Forbes World's Richest People list.



